In a medium saucepan, melt butter over medium heat. Saute green pepper and mushrooms until pepper are crisp-tender. Meanwhile, mix together flour and seasonings; stir into vegetables. Cook and stir until flour is moistened. Stir in broth and milk. Cook, stirring constantly, until thickened. Add turkey and peas; heat through. Gently stir in pimientos. Spoon into shells and serve immediately.